Full licence texts
================================================================

This notice lists, for each component, the licence and the principal copyright
holder(s). The full text of each licence is available from the linked project
homepage; for the components bundled inside Electron (Chromium, Node.js, FFmpeg)
it is in the LICENSES files shipped inside the Electron distribution. Most npm
components also carry their own upstream LICENSE file in the packaged app
(node_modules / resources).

Some components are vendored inside another package and do not ship a separate
licence file of their own — notably libuiohook (LGPL-3.0, inside the uiohook-napi
native addon) and the upstream RNNoise library (BSD-3-Clause, compiled into
@timephy/rnnoise-wasm). Their licence and attribution are recorded above.
Assembling the complete verbatim upstream licence texts into the shipped
distribution — including the LGPL-2.1 (FFmpeg) and LGPL-3.0 (libuiohook) texts —
is tracked as a follow-up. If you require the complete corresponding source for
any LGPL component, contact legal@hakospace.com.
